sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant React as React Frontend
    participant Main as Main Server
    participant DB as Main SQLite
    participant Strat as WorkerSelectionStrategy
    participant Worker as Chosen Worker
    participant SplitDB as Worker Split-DB

    React->>Main: POST /API/V1/Companies<br/>Authorization: Bearer <WorkerJwt-or-MainJwt><br/>X-Correlation-Id, X-Idempotency-Key (ULID)<br/>{ CompanyCode, CompanyName, OwnerUserId, ... }
    Main->>Main: Validate session + payload<br/>Idempotency cache lookup (TTL=86400s per spec/19/15)
    Main->>DB: SELECT eligible WorkerNode rows
    DB-->>Main: candidates
    Main->>Strat: pick(candidates, strategyCode)
    Strat-->>Main: WorkerNode (id=3)
    Main->>DB: INSERT Company (minimal identity, WorkerNodeId=3)
    Main->>DB: INSERT WorkerSelectionEvent
    Main->>Worker: POST /Internal/Company<br/>Authorization: Bearer <internal-JWT><br/>X-Correlation-Id, X-Idempotency-Key
    Worker->>SplitDB: Create RootCompany + AppCompanyShard
    SplitDB-->>Worker: ok
    Worker-->>Main: 201 Created (CompanyId)
    Main-->>React: 201 JSON { Data: { CompanyId, WorkerNodeId, AssignedSubdomain }, Meta: { CorrelationId, IdempotencyReplay: false } }
    Note over React: NO new WorkerJwt is minted by this flow.<br/>React continues using the existing in-memory JWT<br/>(spec/19/12-jwt-delivery-contract.md §2).<br/>For the new tenant React calls /Company/{slug}/Resolve to obtain a JWT scoped to it.

    Note over Main,Worker: Failure path: if Worker returns 5xx, Main retries<br/>(MaxAttempts=3, backoff [2,8,30]s per spec/19/15-tunable-constants.md)<br/>then surfaces WorkerUnreachable (WORKER-300-02) per spec/19/13-error-codes.md.<br/>Idempotency replay returns the original response with X-Idempotency-Replay: true.
